h4. Problem
Our documentation for [connecting JIRA to MySQL|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Connecting+JIRA+to+MySQL] states:
{quote}*Binary logging* — Be aware that JIRA uses the 'READ-COMMITTED' transaction isolation level with MySQL, which currently only supports row-based binary logging. If you require MySQL's binary logging features, you must configure MySQL's binary logging format to be 'row-based'. If not, you may encounter problems when creating issues in JIRA. For more information, please refer to [JIRA Cannot Create Issues when Using MySQL with Binary Logging|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRAKB/JIRA+Cannot+Create+Issues+when+Using+MySQL+with+Binary+Logging].{quote}

The [referenced KB article|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRAKB/JIRA+Cannot+Create+Issues+when+Using+MySQL+with+Binary+Logging] mentions a MySQL bug that has been fixed ever since: [http://bugs.mysql.com/bug.php?id=40360]. The fix seemingly have been delivered in versions 5.1.47 and 5.5.5.

h4. Suggestion
As of my local tests, setting {{binlog_format}} to {{row}}, {{statement}} or {{mixed}} all allow the transaction isolation level to be set {{read committed}}, which was the original reason why this suggestion was made.

Since recent versions of MySQL all work with this setting, I believe it is best to adjust the wording of the recommendation, specifying that using a recent version of MySQL can be a solution, instead of the applied workaround (changing binlog_format).

